article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho -- — Brayden Parker scored 20 points as Idaho State beat Sacramento State 68-40 on Thursday night. Parker had five rebounds for the Bengals (10-14, 5-6 Big Sky Conference). Miguel Tomley scored 13 points while going 5 of 11 (3 for 8 from 3-point range), and added five rebounds. Maleek Arington was 4 of 7 shooting (4 for 4 from 3-point range) to finish with 13 points, while adding eight assists and four steals. The Hornets (6-18, 2-9) were led by Bowyn Beatty, who recorded seven points and six rebounds. Alex Kovatchev added six points for Sacramento State. In addition, Duncan Powell finished with six points. The Hornets prolonged their losing streak to seven straight. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
